    Chojnacky (1985)

    chojnacky_1985.Rd

    Allometric models from Chojnacky (1985)

    Stem Volume Models

    vsa = (a + b * (dsoc^2 * hst))^3

    • vsa [ft3] - volume of the entire stem, including top and stump

    • dsoc [in] - diameter outside bark above the root collar

    • hst [ft] - total height of the stem

    vsa = (a + b * (dsoc^2 * hst + c * single_stem))^3

    • vsa [ft3] - volume of the entire stem, including top and stump

    • dsoc [in] - diameter outside bark above the root collar

    • hst [ft] - total height of the stem

    • single_stem [] - Equal to 1 if the tree has one stem, 0 otherwise
